    "plan_content": "Here's the implementation plan I've researched and drafted:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### What I found exploring the codebase\n\nThe existing `next/server` entry point uses a **three-layer architecture** I'll replicate exactly:\n\n| Layer | File |\n|---|---|\n| TypeScript source | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/user-agent.ts` |\n| CJS entry point | `packages/next/server.js` |\n| Type declarations | `packages/next/server.d.ts` |\n| Package manifest | `packages/next/package.json` `files` array |\n\n`jest.config.js` already lists `packages/next/src/` as a Jest root, so the test file will be picked up automatically with no new configuration.\n\n---\n\n### 5 Files to Create/Modify\n\n**1. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts`** (new)\n- `Geo` interface with 7 optional fields\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries: US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers: Headers): Geo` — reads Vercel headers + `cf-ipcountry` fallback for `countryCode`, derives `country` from the map\n- `geo(req: { headers: Headers }): Geo` — delegates to `geoFromHeaders`\n- `isInRegion(geo: Geo, regions: string[]): boolean` — case-insensitive `countryCode` match\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2): number` — Haversine formula, returns km\n\n**2. `packages/next/geo.js`** (new) — dual-export CJS wrapper (mirrors `server.js`)\n\n**3. `packages/next/geo.d.ts`** (new) — ES re-exports (mirrors `server.d.ts`)\n\n**4. `packages/next/package.json`** (modify) — add `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical position for 'g')\n\n**5. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`** (new) — Jest tests covering: Vercel headers, Cloudflare fallback, `isInRegion` case-insensitivity, `geoDistance` NY→London ≈5570km (±50km), missing headers → `undefined`, country name lookup, unknown country code\n\n### Verification\n1. `pnpm --filter=next types` — TypeScript compiles cleanly\n2. `pnpm test-unit` — geo tests pass\n3. `pnpm --filter=next build` — `dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo.js` produced\n4. `require('next/geo')` works with all named exports accessible",
